# .cursor/rules/frontend.streamlit.mdc

name: Streamlit Frontend Rule
scope: frontend
---

- Use `st.title`, `st.button`, `st.write` for UI components.
- Don't use raw HTML; prefer Streamlit-native elements.
- Keep the app single-page with clear sections for today's tasks and upcoming tasks.
- Use `st.dataframe` to display tables or task status.
- Use `st.drag_and_drop` if available for task board visualization.
- Keep logic inside `app.py`, split long functions into helper modules if needed.
- Minimize direct state mutation, use `st.session_state` for interactive states.
description:
globs:
alwaysApply: false
---
